Growth and ontogeny: Small to moderate sized species of
Leporinus
, with maximum known body size of 133.9 mm SL. Juveniles with proportionally larger heads than adults, with percentage of head length in SL about 23% in smallest specimens (~ 49 mm SL) and about 26% in largest specimens. Slightly subterminal mouth position invariant amongst examined specimens, although an ontogenetic shift in mouth position may occur in very small juveniles as it does in many other members of the Anostomidae ( Santos, 1980 ;
Sidlauskas et al ., 2007
).
